{
  "texts": [
    "L1 and L2 regularization include penalty terms into the loss function depending on weight magnitudes, discouraging big weights and encouraging sparsity.",
    "These strategies work together to increase robust training and generalization, both of which are critical components of developing effective and dependable neural network models.Optimization techniques are critical in neural network training because they determine how model parameters should be updated to minimize the loss function and improve prediction performance.",
    "The cornerstone is Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD), which iteratively updates parameters in the opposite direction as the gradient of the loss function.",
    "Adam, a popular method, combines the advantages of momentum and RMSProp, providing customizable learning rates for specific parameters and demonstrating efficacy across a broad variety of situations.",
    "Prop modifies learning rates depending on the size of current gradients, whereas Adagrad adapts rates using historical gradient information, which is especially useful for sparse data."
  ]
}